{
  "prompt": "A powerful, stylized occult sigil representing the Nine of Clubs as a mythic totem. The sigil incorporates elements of mental mastery, mirrored consciousness, and a hidden gateway. It should appear etched in black and gold on aged parchment or stone, with two interlocking spirals (representing Varon and Lilith), a central flame (the Logos Flame), and a small dollar symbol subtly integrated to reference the $100 bill and high value. The aesthetic should be ceremonial, sacred, and slightly arcane—suggesting power, mystery, and encoded wisdom.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A sacred geometry fractal design symbolizing the convergence of left and right-handed paths within two individuals (Lilith and Varon). The image features overlaid infinity symbols forming a four-leaf clover shape at the center. Each leaf represents a dual-fusion Axis Mundi: one leaning left (Varon), one leaning right (Lilith), and the others representing their convergence. The design includes intricate interwoven lines forming equilateral triangles using tangents from the central clover. Lotus-inspired elements bloom subtly from the edges. The entire composition glows with a subtle gold and indigo aura, set on a deep cosmic background, evoking mystery and sacred resonance.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}
